 67,715 N0506 h0504o! 010502020605070401Welcome to Chinese for HSK Level 1 - a Chinese course for beginners. My name is YU Bin. I am very happy to meet you here!  

HSK stands for H0102ny0500 (Chinese) Shu0506p0102ng (level) K0504osh0101 (test), which is the most important Chinese proficiency test in use today. It assesses non-native Chinese speakers090005 abilities in using Chinese in their daily, academic and professional lives. 

Chinese for HSK Level 1 is the first part of the 6 levels and assesses test takers090005 abilities in the application of everyday Chinese. It is the counterpart of Level 1 of the Chinese Language Proficiency Scales for Speakers of Other Languages and the A1 Level of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages. You will learn:

070304	30 video lectures with dialogue role plays by PKU students; 
070304	More than 150 commonly used words; 
070304	Around 50 key grammar points;
070304	New words and texts via audio; 
070304	Quizzes for each lesson and HSK test papers;
070304	Videos for 70 basic Chinese characters (optional);
070304	Supplementary materials about China (optional).

In short, the course covers the four skills although only listening and reading are tested in HSK. At the end of the course, you will be able to understand and use simple Chinese phrases, meet basic needs for communication and possess the ability to further your Chinese language studies. 

Have a fantastic journey of Chinese learning.                                                  

For more information about HSK please visit: http://english.hanban.org/node_7581.htm.
